txt.en: Return to Sergeant Hubyrt of Wakenflood

'When the Easterlings raided Wakenflood, they dragged off several of our warriors. These are proud men and brave; they should not be shackled like slaves.\n\n'I shudder to think what the Easterlings might want with these men: torture, starve them? Please do what you can to get into their camp and free the imprisoned warriors of Wakenflood!'

'You are a true hero, [placeholder]. These men did not deserve to meet whatever fate those Easterlings had in store for them.\n\n'Their wives and children in Harwick will be forever grateful for what you did this day.'
Several prisoners from Wakenflood were taken by the Easterlings to Olghakhósh, their newly-sprung encampment on the banks of the Anduin.
Prisoners from Wakenflood can be found in the Easterling encampment of Olghakhósh on the banks of the Anduin.\n\nYou should find and free as many prisoners as you can in Olghakhósh.
Sergeant Hubyrt can be found in Wakenflood in the Wold.\n\nYou should return to Sergeant Hubyrt along with the men you freed.
